        "content": "<p>I'd like to add a builtin List function with this type:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Haskell\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kt\">List</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">elem</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"ow\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Result</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">elem</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">List</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">elem</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"kt\">ListWasEmpty</span><span class=\"p\">]</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>so it gives you back the first element in the list followed by the rest of the list after it (as a seamless slice).</p>\n<p>I specifically want this for parsers - it's a nice way to use a single conditional to advance to the next element in the list - although it may have other use cases.</p>",
        "id": 400325138,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1699129569
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I definitely do not want to introduce special pattern matching syntax for this like Elm and Haskell have.</p>",
        "id": 400325140,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1699129575
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>anyone have thoughts on what a good name would be for this function?</p>",
        "id": 400325146,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1699129589
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>for reference, here are <a href=\"https://www.roc-lang.org/builtins/List\">the current List operations</a></p>",
        "id": 400325151,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1699129600
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>It’s similar to <a href=\"https://package.elm-lang.org/packages/elm/core/latest/String#uncons\">String.uncons</a> in Elm, but that’s a pretty bad name</p>",
        "id": 400325507,
        "sender_full_name": "Agus Zubiaga",
        "timestamp": 1699130016
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Too bad <code>List.splitFirst</code> is already taken</p>",
        "id": 400325557,
        "sender_full_name": "Agus Zubiaga",
        "timestamp": 1699130049
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>What about <code>List.splitHead</code> or <code>List.headAndTail</code>?</p>",
        "id": 400325862,
        "sender_full_name": "Isaac Van Doren",
        "timestamp": 1699130521
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><code>popFirst</code> and <code>popLast</code> are maybe interesting</p>",
        "id": 400325988,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1699130654
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I do like that those names work for the first and last elements</p>",
        "id": 400326011,
        "sender_full_name": "Isaac Van Doren",
        "timestamp": 1699130714
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Don't we already have pattern matching syntax for this?</p>",
        "id": 400327523,
        "sender_full_name": "Brendan Hansknecht",
        "timestamp": 1699132561
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><code>[head, .. as rest]</code></p>",
